{{Infobox film | name = Being in the World | image = Being in the World.jpg | caption = | director = [[Tao Ruspoli]] | producer = [[Giancarlo Canavesio]], [[Christopher Redlich]] | writer = | starring = | cinematography = [[Christopher Gallo]] | editing = [[Paul Forte]], Tao Ruspoli | released = 2010 | runtime = 81 minutes | country = United States | language = English }}
'''''Being in the World''''' is a 2010 [[documentary film]] directed by [[Tao Ruspoli]]. The film is based on [[Martin Heidegger]]'s philosophy and is inspired by [[Hubert Dreyfus]]. It features a number of prominent philosophers.<ref>[http://www.brooklynfilmfestival.org/films/detail.asp?fid=1048 BEING IN THE WORLD]</ref>
Philosophers such as [[Hubert Dreyfus]], [[Mark Wrathall]], [[Sean Dorrance Kelly]], [[Taylor Carman]], [[John Haugeland]], [[Iain Thomson]], [[Charles Taylor (philosopher)|Charles Taylor]] and [[Albert Borgmann]] are featured in the film. Other people featured in the film include [[Ryan Cross]], [[Leah Chase]], [[Manuel Molina]], [[Hiroshi Sakaguchi]], [[Jumane Smith]], [[Austin Peralta]], [[Bob Teague]], [[Lindsey Banner]] and [[Elizabeth Gilbert]].
