{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Use Australian English|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox rugby league biography |name = Harold Angus |fullname = Harold Angus |birth_date = 1892 |birth_place = [[Sydney, New South Wales]] |death_date = 17 Aug 1979 |death_place = [[Yowie Bay, New South Wales]] |retired = yes |position = {{rlp|LK}} |club1 = [[Glebe (rugby league team)|Glebe]] |year1start = 1916 |year1end = 20 |appearances1 = 14 |tries1 = 1 |goals1 = 0 |fieldgoals1 = 0 |points1 = 3 |source = <ref>https://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/harold-angus/summary.html</ref> }}
'''Harold Angus''' (1892-1979) was an Australian rugby league player for the [[Glebe (rugby league team)|Glebe]] club in the early years of the [[NSWRFL]] competition.
A local junior, Harold Angus was a tough forward who played for the [[Glebe (rugby league team)|Glebe]] Dirty Red's for many years and captained [[Glebe (rugby league team)|Glebe]] Reserve Grade sides to premiership victory in 1918 and 1919. He retired in the early 1920s.<ref>Alan Whiticker & Glen Hudson: The Encyclopedia of Rugby League Players. 1995 {{ISBN|1875169571}}</ref><ref>https://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/harold-angus/summary.html</ref>
Angus was often used as a first grade replacement player for Club Captain [[Frank Burge]].<ref>Referee (Sydney) 20 June 1917 "Glebe Captain has Broken Arm". https://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/120295803?searchTerm=harold%20angus%20glebe&searchLimits=</ref>
Harold Angus died in the Sutherland Shire on 17 August 1979 and was interred at [[Rookwood Cemetery]] on 20 Aug 1979.<ref>Sydney Morning Herald, Death Notice:18 Aug 1979</ref>
