This is a list of many, but not all, of the assassinated Lebanese political figures:
*[[Fouad Jumblatt]] - a leader in the [[Chouf District]], and father of [[Kamal Jumblatt]], later assassinated as well. Assassinated on 6 August 1921. *[[Riad Al Solh]] - first prime minister of Lebanon. Assassinated on 17 July 1951. *[[Maarouf Saad]] - Mayor of [[Sidon]] and founder of the [[Popular Nasserist Organization]]. Shot by a sniper on 26 February 1975 and died on 6 March 1975.<ref name="maarouf-saad-foundation">{{cite news|url=http://www.maaroufsaadfoundation.org/bio.html|title=Maarouf Saad Foundation|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110307014451/http://maaroufsaadfoundation.org/bio.html|archivedate=2011-03-07|df=}}</ref> ''See [[Lebanese Civil War]]''. *[[Kamal Jumblatt]] - founder of [[Progressive Socialist Party (Lebanon)|Progressive Socialist Party]]. Assassinated on 16 March 1977.<ref name=lebaneseassassinations/> *[[Tony Frangieh]] - son of former President [[Suleiman Frangieh]]. Assassinated on 13 June 1978, known as [[Ehden massacre|Ehden Massacre]].<ref name=lebaneseassassinations/> *[[Salim Lawzi]] - journalist. Assassinated some time between 24 February and 6 March 1980.<ref name=lebaneseassassinations>{{cite web|title=Assassinations in Lebanon: A History (1970s to the Present)|url=http://middleeast.about.com/od/lebanon/a/me090303.htm|publisher=About.com|accessdate=30 June 2012}}</ref> *[[Riad Taha]] - journalist and president of the Lebanese Publishers Association. Assassinated on 23 July 1980.<ref name=lebaneseassassinations/> *[[Bachir Gemayel]] - former President-Elect, founder of [[Lebanese Forces]], son of [[Pierre Gemayel]]. Assassinated on 14 September 1982. *Sheikh Ahmad Assaf - Lebanese Sunni cleric. Assassinated in April 1982.<ref name=nassif2001>{{cite journal|last=Gambill|first=Gary C.|author2=Daniel Nassif |title=Syria's Campaign to Silence Lebanese Muslims|journal=Middle East Intelligence Bulletin|date=April 2001|volume=3|issue=4|url=http://www.meforum.org/meib/articles/0104_l1.htm|accessdate=21 October 2012}}</ref> *[[Ragheb Harb]] - was a Lebanese resistance leader and Muslim cleric.Assassinated on 16 February 1984. *Sobhi Saleh - head of the Sunni Islamic Higher Council. Assassinated on October 1986.<ref name=lebaneseassassinations/> *[[Rashid Karami]] - former Prime Minister. Assassinated on 1 June 1987.<ref>{{cite news|title=Prime Minister Karami killed|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1842&dat=19870602&id=Vk8gAAAAIBAJ&sjid=8cgEAAAAIBAJ&pg=4744,220083|accessdate=26 January 2014|newspaper=Times Daily|date=2 June 1987}}</ref> *[[Mohammad Choucair]] - adviser to the former President [[Amine Gemayel]]. Assassinated on 2 August 1987.<ref name=lgic>{{cite web|title=Assassination of Mohammad Choucair|url=http://www.lgic.org/en/help_syria_terrorism.php|publisher=LGIC|accessdate=15 March 2013}}</ref> *[[Hassan Khaled]] - former Grand Mufti of Lebanon's Sunni Muslim community. Assassinated on 16 May 1989.<ref name=nassif2001/> *Nazem el Qadri - member of the Lebanese Parliament. Assassinated on 22 September 1989.<ref name=lebaneseassassinations/> *[[René Moawad]] - former Lebanese president. Assassinated on 22 November 1989. *[[Dany Chamoun]] - leader of National Liberal Party, son of [[Camille Chamoun]]. Assassinated on 21 October 1990. *[[Abbas al-Musawi]] - leader of [[Hezbollah]]. Assassinated on 16 February 1992. *[[Elie Hobeika]] - militia commander, politician. Assassinated on 24 January 2002. *[[Ramzi Irani]] - Lebanese Forces student representative at [[Lebanese University]]. Assassinated on 7 May 2002. *[[Rafik Hariri]] and [[Bassel Fleihan]] - former Lebanese Prime Minister and Former Minister, respectively. Assassinated on 14 February 2005. *[[Samir Kassir]] - university professor, journalist and historian. Assassinated on 2 June 2005. *[[George Hawi]] - former secretary general of the [[Lebanese Communist Party]] (LCP). Assassinated on 21 June 2005. *[[Gebran Tueni]] - politician and newspaper editor. Assassinated on 12 December 2005. *[[Pierre Amine Gemayel]] - Minister of Industry and leader of [[Kataeb]]. Assassinated on 21 November 2006. *[[Walid Eido]] - parliament Member. Assassinated on 13 June 2007. *[[Antoine Ghanem]] - parliament Member. Assassinated on 19 September 2007. *[[François al-Hajj]] - Brigadier General of the [[Lebanese Army]]. Assassinated on 12 December 2007. *Wissam Eid - an officer in the Internal Security Forces investigating the 2005 Hariri assassination. Assassinated on 25 January 2008. *[[Imad Mughniyah]] - senior [[Hezbollah]] member. Assassinated on 12 February 2008. *[[Saleh al Aridi]] - a leader of the Lebanese Democratic Party. Assassinated on 10 September 2008. *[[Wissam al-Hassan]], head of information branch of [[Internal Security Forces|the Internal Security Forces]]. Assassinated on 19 October 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/oct/19/lebanon-divide-assassination-security-chief|title=Lebanon's great divide exposed by assassination of security chief|last=Chulov|first=Martin|date=19 October 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref> * [[Hassan al-Laqqis]]- was a military commander of [[Hezbollah]]. Assassinated between 3 and 4 December 2013. *[[Mohamad Chatah]] - Former Lebanese Finance Minister and critic of Syria and Hezbollah. A senior adviser to the Sunni Future politician Saad Hariri. Assassinated on 27 December 2013.
